---
export const prerender = true;

import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts';
---

<ServiceLayout
	title={`Custom AI Solutions | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
	description="Privacy-focused AI that runs on your hardware. Self-hosted intelligence without the corporate surveillance."
>
	<div class="header-section">
		<div class="icon-header">
			<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
				<rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/>
				<path d="M9 9h6v6H9z"/>
				<path d="M9 1v2M15 1v2M9 21v2M15 21v2M20 9h2M20 15h2M1 9h2M1 15h2"/>
				<circle cx="12" cy="12" r="1.5" fill="currentColor"/>
			</svg>
		</div>
		<h1>Custom AI Solutions</h1>
	</div>
	<p class="intro">
		Privacy-focused AI that runs on your hardware. Self-hosted intelligence without the corporate surveillance.
	</p>

	<section class="overview">
		<h2>What This Offers</h2>
		<p>
			AI doesn't have to mean sending your data to third-party APIs. Whether you need a personal
			research assistant, a private chatbot, or custom document analysis—you can run powerful AI
			models on your own infrastructure.
		</p>
		<p>
			From integrating commercial APIs (OpenAI, Anthropic) to deploying fully self-hosted open-source
			models, the approach depends on your privacy requirements and hardware constraints.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="capabilities">
		<h2>Capabilities</h2>
		<div class="grid">
			<div class="capability">
				<h3>LLM Integration</h3>
				<p>
					Custom chatbots, RAG pipelines, and knowledge bases. Integrate OpenAI, Anthropic, or
					open-source models into your existing workflows with complete control over prompts and outputs.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="capability">
				<h3>Self-Hosted Inference</h3>
				<p>
					Deploy models with vLLM, Ollama, or custom inference servers. GPU optimization, quantization
					strategies, and scaling for personal or small team use.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="capability">
				<h3>RAG & Knowledge Systems</h3>
				<p>
					Vector databases, document preprocessing, and retrieval pipelines. Turn your private documents
					into queryable knowledge bases without leaking data to external services.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="ideal-for">
		<h2>Ideal For</h2>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Personal Research Assistants:</strong> Query your notes, documents, and research privately</li>
			<li><strong>Local Chatbots:</strong> Custom AI assistants running entirely on your hardware</li>
			<li><strong>Document Analysis:</strong> Process sensitive documents without cloud services</li>
			<li><strong>Code Assistance:</strong> Self-hosted copilot alternatives for development work</li>
			<li><strong>Learning & Experimentation:</strong> Hands-on experience with modern AI without vendor lock-in</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="example">
		<h2>Privacy-First Approach</h2>
		<p>
			The most powerful AI models require significant compute, but recent advances in quantization
			and efficient inference mean you can run capable models on consumer hardware. Whether you're
			using a cloud GPU or a local desktop with a decent graphics card, self-hosted AI is increasingly
			practical.
		</p>
		<p>
			For less demanding use cases or when maximum capability is needed, API integrations provide a
			middle ground—but with proper data handling, prompt engineering, and output validation to maintain
			control over your workflows.
		</p>
	</section>
</ServiceLayout>
